$ SARS-CoV-2 Spike Glycoprotein

The spike glycoprotein is a surface protein that enables the SARS-CoV-2 virus to attach and enter host cells. It is one of the most important viral proteins studied in vaccine and antiviral drug development.

This sequence is useful for protein structure prediction, molecular docking, mutation analysis, and epitope mapping studies. It is also widely used in computational virology and immunoinformatics research.
